Meet Amy @lefevrediary
\xe2\x80\x9cMy name is Amy Julliette Lefe\xcc\x81vre. I am a model and content creator based in NYC, but my family is originally from West Africa and Belgium where I grew up. I love the creativity of fashion, the art of travel, and finding ways to get inspired in little ways every day. While we are all facing so many difficult issues at the moment, I am currently very inspired to see all the solidarity around the world to support social and racial justice. I have personally faced racism and discrimination growing up and professionally, so the unity to reject hate gives me confidence that together we can all bring about critical change.\xe2\x80\x9d'

Meet Jennifer @jenniferatilemile
\xe2\x80\x9cI grew up in Australia, and now call New York home. In Australia I didn\xe2\x80\x99t see anyone that looked like me growing up - and as a result, I struggled a lot with my identity. I embarked on a journey of discovery about six years ago, and claiming and owning my blackness was one of the most powerful things I\xe2\x80\x99ve done. My goal as a model has always been to be the woman that I didn\xe2\x80\x99t see growing up. I want women like me to feel seen, because if you can\xe2\x80\x99t see it you can\xe2\x80\x99t believe it."'

Meet Taelor @taelorthein
\xe2\x80\x9cI loved growing up in the Midwest but being a mixed child growing up in Iowa was very confusing for me, no doubt. I was very self aware from a very young age that I was different. As a young adult looking back I realize there were instances of discrimination that I\xe2\x80\x99ve shrugged off and haven\xe2\x80\x99t allowed myself to feel and therefore heal from. Luckily I ALWAYS had my mom to have my back. I\xe2\x80\x99m so grateful for the love from my family and friends I had surrounding me. I\xe2\x80\x99m proud of all of the makings that make me (German, Scottish, Irish, Cameroonian) and what has shaped me into the woman I am today.\xe2\x80\x9d'
